  "prompt": "Upto which rank does a reserved category student get IRS (IT)?",
  "response": "In the IRS (Income Tax) recruitment process, reserved category candidates get relaxation in the upper age limit and number of attempts as per government norms. However, for the final selection, the general cutoff rank applies to all candidates, regardless of category. \n\nTypically, reserved category candidates can get IRS (IT) if they:\n1. Meet the minimum qualifying marks\n2. Rank within the total available vacancies\n3. Fulfill all eligibility criteria\n\nThe exact rank depends on:\n- Total number of vacancies\n- Performance in the examination\n- Category-wise reservation policy\n\nFor precise details, I recommend checking the official UPSC notification for the specific year of recruitment, as the exact ranks can vary between different recruitment cycles.",
